sentences: Amund originally collaborated with partner Espen Lind in 1997 for Lind’s solo album Red.
In 2001, they solidified this working relationship with the formation of their songwriting and music production team Espionage.
Their next award winning song was co-written for Beyoncé in 2006.
The international hit "Irreplaceable” held the number one spot on the Billboard Hot 100 for ten consecutive weeks and won the pair a  BMI Urban Award for song of the year in 2008.

Espionage’s success continued with the co-writing of Chris Brown’s hit  With You in 2007.

In 2018, along with Stargate producer Tor Erik Hermansen and composer Magnus Beite, Amund developed and opened the Lillehammer Institute of Music Production and Industries, also known as LIMPI, in Lillehammer.
